Sure, here is a description of the specialty 191 "Архітектура та будівництво" at the Kharkiv School of Architecture, based on the provided criteria:

**1. Description of the Specialty**

The specialty 191 "Architecture and Construction" encompasses a broad spectrum of knowledge and skills necessary for the design, construction, and operation of buildings and structures. Specialists in this field are involved in all stages of a building's life cycle, from conceptual design to commissioning and ongoing maintenance.

**Duties of an architect and builder include:**

* Developing architectural projects for buildings and structures, including drawings, models, and technical documentation;
* Analyzing building codes, regulations, and standards;
* Conducting site surveys on construction sites;
* Determining materials and technologies for construction;
* Controlling the quality of construction work;
* Preparing the necessary documentation for putting the building into operation.

**2. Educational Program of the Specialty**

The educational program of the specialty 191 "Architecture and Construction" includes a wide range of theoretical and practical disciplines necessary for training high-level specialists. Students study subjects such as:

* Architectural design;
* Structural design;
* Building materials and technologies;
* Building engineering equipment;
* Urban planning;
* Construction economics;
* Design basics;
* History of architecture;
* Building law.

Education in the specialty 191 "Architecture and Construction" involves internships at construction sites, architectural bureaus, and design organizations.

**3. Career Prospects for the Specialty**

Architects and builders are in constant demand in the labor market in Ukraine and abroad. Specialists in this specialty can work in various fields, including design, construction, real estate, public service, and education.

**Promising career directions for architects and builders include:**

* Design of buildings and structures for various purposes;
* Construction and reconstruction of residential buildings, industrial facilities, and infrastructure facilities;
* Expertise of construction projects;
* Organization and management of construction projects;
* Teaching architectural and construction disciplines in higher educational institutions.

Graduates with a diploma in the specialty 191 "Architecture and Construction" have high chances of employment and can expect competitive salaries.
